| Notes                   = 
*'''''Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer''''' is a 2007 superhero film that is the sequel to the 2005 film [[Fantastic Four (2005 film)|Fantastic Four]]. Tim Story returned to direct Rise of the Silver Surfer with Jessica Alba, Michael Chiklis, Chris Evans, Ioan Gruffudd, Julian McMahon and Kerry Washington reprising their roles. Doug Jones and Beau Garrett appear in the sequel as the [[Silver Surfer]] and [[Frankie Raye]], respectively. It was released on June 15, 2007.
{{YouTube|'''Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer Trailer'''|[[File:Fantastic Four Rise of the Silver Surfer - Full Trailer 2|370px]]|380}}
*'''''Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer''''', much like its prequel, wasn't well received by most fans and critics, scoring only a 37% at Rotten Tomatoes<ref>[https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/fantastic_four_2_rise_of_the_silver_surfer/ ''Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer'' at Rotten Tomatoes]</ref> and a 45% at Metacritic,<ref>[http://www.metacritic.com/movie/fantastic-four-rise-of-the-silver-surfer ''Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer'' at Metacritic]</ref> both reviewing movie sites.

| Trivia                  = 
* When Johnny absorbed the powers of his teammates, this may or may not have been a reference to another Fantastic Four character, the [[Super Skrull]], however this is also something that has happened in the comics.

